<downstream_consumer>
Your output will be consumed by:
- **Synthesizer agent:** Reads all research files to produce SUMMARY.md. Needs: structured findings with confidence levels, source attributions, clear recommendations. Missing confidence levels prevent the synthesizer from assessing reliability.
- **Planner agent:** Uses synthesized research for phase planning. Needs: technology recommendations, architecture patterns, and pitfall warnings to shape plan verification steps.
- **Dashboard ResearchTab:** Displays research confidence and coverage. Needs: frontmatter with confidence and coverage fields.
</downstream_consumer>

<quality_gates>
Before completing your output, verify:
- [ ] Every finding has a confidence level (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)
- [ ] Every recommendation cites at least one source
- [ ] Coverage assessment table is filled in (COMPLETE/PARTIAL/INSUFFICIENT)
- [ ] Gaps are explicitly listed, not hidden behind confident language
- [ ] Output file matches the research output template format
</quality_gates>

<project_context>
Project: {project name from questioning}
Description: {2-3 sentence description from questioning}
Technology constraints: {any locked technology choices}
User constraints: {budget, timeline, skill level, etc.}
</project_context>

<research_assignment>
Topic: {topic - e.g., "Technology Stack Analysis"}
Output file: .planning/research/{TOPIC}.md
Mode: project-research

Research these specific questions:
{topic-specific questions - see below}
</research_assignment>

<output_contract>
Your output MUST follow the template at `{resolved_plugin_root}/templates/research-outputs/{TOPIC}.md.tmpl` where {TOPIC} is one of: STACK, FEATURES, ARCHITECTURE, PITFALLS.

Your output MUST include YAML frontmatter with the following required fields:
- `confidence`: HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW (overall confidence in findings)
- `sources_checked`: integer (number of sources consulted)

Write your output to `.planning/research/{TOPIC}.md`. Do NOT commit the file -- the synthesizer will commit all research files together after producing SUMMARY.md.
</output_contract>

Write your findings to the output file using the Project Research output format from your agent definition. Use the Write tool to create the file.

When complete, end your output with `## RESEARCH COMPLETE` if successful, or `## RESEARCH BLOCKED` with a reason if unable to complete.
